RIO DE JANEIRO
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-Americon artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the becutiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad
RIO DE JANEIRO is the jewel of South America. Nowhere in the world is a city blessed with so much
natural beauty Corcovado Mountain, crowned by the imposing statue of Christ the Redeemer, and
Sugar Loaf, overlocking Guanabara Bay and the city lights below, are equally breathtoking sights.
Rio is also renowned for its magnificent beaches. Gavea Beach, the site of the luxurious
Inter-Continental-Rio, and Copacabana Beach, with its mosaic walks, are world famous. Pan Am
serves Rio daily from New York Washington, Miami, San Francisco, Los Angeles, and Houston.
